<div style="width: 600px; max-height: 550px; overflow-x: auto;"><h1 class="green b_mar_ten">THE MAD SCIENTIST'S GUIDE TO WORLD DOMINATION</h1>
	<p class="size11"><strong>Room: HALL C (602-603)</strong><em><br/>Start: 1:20PM<br/>End: 2:15PM</em></p><br/>
	<p class="rte">Join Wired.com's very own mad scientist, <b>John Joseph Adams </b>(co-host of "Geek's Guide To The Galaxy") as he welcomes best selling authors and fellow mad scientists <b>Chris Claremont</b> ("X-Men", "Chronicles of the Shadow War" trilogy), <b>Seanan McGuire</b> ("Rosemary and Rue") and <b>Daniel H. Wilson </b>("Robopocalypse") to show you the ins and outs of World Domination! John will talk about his new book, appropriately titled "The Mad Scientist's Guide to World Domination" which features both Mr. Claremont and Mr. Wilson. Topics may include, "White Lab Coats: Fashion Statement or Fashion Faux Pas?", "How To Keep Your Minions From Unionizing" and "Self Experimentation, The Time Is Now!"</p></div>